org.cast.cwm.data
Class Response

java.lang.Object
  org.cast.cwm.data.PersistedObject
      org.cast.cwm.data.Response
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
@Entity
public class Response
extends PersistedObject

A Response represents a single chunk of user input; a response to a Prompt object. Each Response refers to an active ResponseData object for its actual content; there may be inactive ResponseData objects that record a history of changes to this Response.

Method Detail

getNewResponseDataObject

public ResponseData getNewResponseDataObject()
Generates a new ResponseData object to be used with this Response. This Response object will automatically point to the new ResponseData object, so calling this method will effectively "erase" the previous ResponseData. TODO: It would be cool to tie this in with a setText() method so that Response would work properly with PropertyModels and Forms. Perhaps a transient ResponseData that is generated once per request and setText(), setScore(), etc all use this transient field that is persisted as the new ResponseData. This would allow us to drop all the methods in ResponseService.

Returns:

isCorrect

public boolean isCorrect()
Return true if this Response is "correct". A response is considered correct if it is scored, and its score is equal to the total points available.

Returns:
true if correct

getTriesOrdinal

public String getTriesOrdinal()
Returns a string like "2nd try" based on the tries field.

Returns:
string value, or empty string if tries is null.
